:{{see|sextans}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the [[astronomer]] Johannes Hevelius in 1690. From {{L.}} ''[[sextans]]'', a "sextant" (''nautical neasuring implement'')

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Sextans}}
'''Sextans'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[dim]] [[spring]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[sextant]]. It lies south of the constellation of [[Leo]].

